758
00:46:56,960 --> 00:46:57,960
Give it to me.

759
00:47:13,840 --> 00:47:14,840
What are you doing?

760
00:47:14,970 --> 00:47:17,280
Oh, yes. I dropped a coin.

761
00:47:17,710 --> 00:47:18,710
Where did it go?

762
00:47:22,150 --> 00:47:23,150
This was yours.

763
00:47:23,820 --> 00:47:26,180
It's good to be thrifty. Right.

764
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:29,120
Hey, Manager!

765
00:47:30,290 --> 00:47:33,030
You found my coin, so I will buy you a drink.

766
00:47:33,790 --> 00:47:34,790
How about it?

767
00:47:35,190 --> 00:47:36,999
- That's good. - Oh, yes.

768
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,430
- Let's go. - Let's go.

769
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,370
So...

770
00:47:45,370 --> 00:47:48,640
Is there only one you found out? The film director's name?

771
00:47:49,110 --> 00:47:50,179
I tried contacting the Film Commission...

772
00:47:50,180 --> 00:47:51,709
and the Independent Film Association,

773
00:47:51,710 --> 00:47:53,310
but they don't have his contact information.

774
00:47:53,980 --> 00:47:57,050
Of all people, that film director's name is Kim Min Su.

775
00:47:57,680 --> 00:47:59,220
It is a very common name in Korea.

776
00:48:02,090 --> 00:48:04,589
Hey, if you search for Kim Min Su...

777
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:07,090
