800
00:49:20,700 --> 00:49:22,200
Oh, you fool.

801
00:49:23,270 --> 00:49:25,000
Why would you break up with someone who is smiling?

802
00:49:26,270 --> 00:49:27,470
How sad.

803
00:49:33,810 --> 00:49:36,380
They say the two of them were close from the beginning.

804
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:38,549
Our CEO as an entertainment CEO.

805
00:49:38,550 --> 00:49:40,290
And Reporter Han as a paid journalist.

806
00:49:42,220 --> 00:49:43,420
A paid journalist?

807
00:49:43,520 --> 00:49:44,990
A journalist who writes articles for money.

808
00:49:45,790 --> 00:49:47,129
He makes potential artists to be famous...

809
00:49:47,130 --> 00:49:48,560
and sends away those unnecessary ones.

810
00:49:50,130 --> 00:49:52,130
So, there were only articles about Yu Ji An...

811
00:49:52,530 --> 00:49:54,130
in his recently written articles.

812
00:49:54,670 --> 00:49:56,769
If a paid reporter publishes a few articles,

813
00:49:56,770 --> 00:49:58,599
the paid commenters rush in and shape public opinion...

814
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:00,269
in the desired direction.

815
00:50:00,270 --> 00:50:01,510
That is how it works.

816
00:50:02,410 --> 00:50:04,679
Anyway, Reporter Han's wealth accumulation...

817
00:50:04,680 --> 00:50:06,910
was thanks to our CEO.

818
00:50:11,220 --> 00:50:15,049
So, Counsellor, do you think the culprit who ruined Ji An...

819
00:50:15,050 --> 00:50:16,860
was my boss?

820
00:50:18,360 --> 00:50:19,360
As you can see,

821
00:50:19,361 --> 00:50:20,890
it is just a suspicion based on circumstantial evidence.

822
00:50:22,690 --> 00:50:24,130
I...

823
00:50:24,430 --> 00:50:25,960
I think...

824
00:50:29,300 --> 00:50:30,400
Oh, it's nothing.

825
00:50:33,070 --> 00:50:37,039
One more thing, our CEO is reporting about Ji An...

826
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:38,040
somewhere.

827
00:50:38,980 --> 00:50:39,980
Reporting?

828
00:50:40,650 --> 00:50:41,650
To whom?

829
00:50:41,880 --> 00:50:43,920
I don't know that.

830
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:46,350
Manager Kim didn't know either.

831
00:50:46,620 --> 00:50:49,349
Is it an unofficial power broker? A mastermind?

832
00:50:49,350 --> 00:50:50,420
That is all he said.

833
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:55,390
But what is that?

834
00:50:55,890 --> 00:50:57,600
Someone is sitting and someone is standing.

835
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:02,930
Oh, it is like a rule in our industry.

836
00:51:03,700 --> 00:51:06,470
The lead actors sit, and the supporting actors stand.

837
00:51:07,140 --> 00:51:09,570
This must be Ji An's first time experiencing something like this.

838
00:51:10,310 --> 00:51:12,409
If it had been the old days, Ji An would have mentioned...

839
00:51:12,410 --> 00:51:14,109
about her class and she would have flipped the set.

840
00:51:14,110 --> 00:51:15,549
And she would have just gone home immediately...

841
00:51:15,550 --> 00:51:17,720
if she had felt bad.

842
00:51:18,850 --> 00:51:20,050
She has changed a lot.

843
00:51:20,950 --> 00:51:22,320
What is popularity?

844
00:51:23,990 --> 00:51:24,990
Indeed.

845
00:51:26,290 --> 00:51:27,690
She has changed so much.

846
00:51:28,530 --> 00:51:30,430
Alright, we will resume filming.

847
00:51:37,140 --> 00:51:38,140
Let's move.

848
00:51:43,880 --> 00:51:44,880
Ready.

849
00:51:46,010 --> 00:51:47,210
Action.

850
00:51:48,050 --> 00:51:50,920
Because of the promotion card the president gave you?

851
00:51:51,350 --> 00:51:52,550
Just for that?

852
00:51:52,820 --> 00:51:53,890
What are you talking about, senior?

853
00:51:54,990 --> 00:51:57,489
You are the one who is doing this...

854
00:51:57,490 --> 00:52:00,030
for a promotion.

855
00:52:02,690 --> 00:52:03,830
Hello, Detective. What's up?

856
00:52:04,730 --> 00:52:05,730
Then you know well?

857
00:52:06,430 --> 00:52:09,070
How you ruined the hard work of many people.

858
00:52:10,000 --> 00:52:11,200
This is your last chance.

859
00:52:12,540 --> 00:52:17,210
- Okay, then let's meet tomorrow. - Cut, cut!

860
00:52:22,450 --> 00:52:24,950
Ji An, your acting is so good this time.

861
00:52:25,450 --> 00:52:27,720
– Really? – It is better than expected.

862
00:52:28,220 --> 00:52:30,520
Let's continue shooting the next scene without needing another take.

863
00:52:31,220 --> 00:52:32,220
Yes.

864
00:53:52,240 --> 00:53:53,970
(Dong Gyeong Kitchen)

865
00:53:55,770 --> 00:53:56,780
Yes, welcome.

866
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:04,220
Oh, Ji An, it has been a while.

867
00:54:08,650 --> 00:54:10,050
Please, have some tea.

868
00:54:12,920 --> 00:54:13,930
Oh, my.

869
00:54:15,090 --> 00:54:16,560
Well...

870
00:54:16,860 --> 00:54:20,430
I don't know much about Eun Hwan's father's accident.

871
00:54:21,670 --> 00:54:22,730
It's a forbidden topic.

872
00:54:23,840 --> 00:54:27,970
You don't know what kind of accident caused his death?

873
00:54:28,570 --> 00:54:30,410
Yes, you know.

874
00:54:30,910 --> 00:54:33,010
Eun Hwan feels guilty about that accident.

875
00:54:34,450 --> 00:54:36,309
He does not bring it up first,

876
00:54:36,310 --> 00:54:38,020
so I felt awkward asking him about it.

877
00:54:39,420 --> 00:54:40,519
What I know is that...

878
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:44,490
Song Hwan was also injured in that accident.

879
00:54:45,860 --> 00:54:47,060
Even his sister...

880
00:54:49,190 --> 00:54:51,159
Then she became disabled...

881
00:54:51,160 --> 00:54:53,130
because of that accident?

882
00:54:53,700 --> 00:54:56,330
Yes, and after that,

883
00:54:57,340 --> 00:55:00,469
Eun Hwan suffered a lot.

884
00:55:00,470 --> 00:55:02,710
His suffering was beyond words.

885
00:55:03,410 --> 00:55:04,410
That's about it.

886
00:55:05,210 --> 00:55:09,050
Eun Hwan must have had a very hard time.

887
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:13,320
Isn't it obvious?

888
00:55:13,990 --> 00:55:16,449
His mother was gone, his father passed away,

889
00:55:16,450 --> 00:55:17,690
and his sister was injured.

890
00:55:18,420 --> 00:55:20,530
He practically lived as a young head of household.

891
00:55:21,590 --> 00:55:24,060
Now, he is doing well on his own,

892
00:55:24,460 --> 00:55:25,899
but that guy has a heartbreaking life story...

893
00:55:25,900 --> 00:55:28,030
that would make you cry.

894
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:30,939
How can you go on a private schedule...

895
00:55:30,940 --> 00:55:32,500
without the manager's permission?

896
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:37,479
Did you forget that tomorrow is the day...

897
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:38,510
of highlight scene filming?

898
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:57,400
Is there any emotion you don't understand?

899
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:04,000
No, not really.

900
00:56:10,610 --> 00:56:14,150
But why did Su Ji leave Jun Ho?

901
00:56:15,210 --> 00:56:16,410
She said she loved him.

902
00:56:18,020 --> 00:56:19,750
She probably left him...

903
00:56:20,298 --> 00:56:21,438
because she loved him.

904
00:56:23,820 --> 00:56:27,360
- Why are you asking it? - That does not make sense.

905
00:56:28,130 --> 00:56:29,590
Leaving because you love someone.

906
00:56:30,660 --> 00:56:32,800
If you love someone, you should stay with them no matter what.

907
00:56:34,830 --> 00:56:39,800
Even if being together makes you both unhappy?

908
00:56:40,810 --> 00:56:44,140
Why would you be unhappy with someone you love?

909
00:56:44,880 --> 00:56:46,440
Not being together is what makes you unhappy.

910
00:56:49,980 --> 00:56:54,650
Because it could be a love that can never come true.

911
00:57:01,460 --> 00:57:03,489
If it can never come true,

912
00:57:03,490 --> 00:57:07,329
then being together would only be a punishment for each other,

913
00:57:07,330 --> 00:57:09,070
wouldn't it?

914
00:57:11,600 --> 00:57:12,600
You're lying.

915
00:57:14,770 --> 00:57:16,209
Where is there such a thing as a love...

916
00:57:16,210 --> 00:57:17,380
that can never come true in this world?

917
00:57:18,240 --> 00:57:20,549
Those are just excuses made...

918
00:57:20,550 --> 00:57:22,480
by people who want to cowardly run away.

919
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:27,820
If I love someone, I will never leave them.

920
00:57:29,648 --> 00:57:30,958
I will stay by their side no matter what.

921
00:57:32,890 --> 00:57:36,360
And I will never forgive anyone...

922
00:57:38,930 --> 00:57:40,530
who says they love me and then leaves.

923
00:57:41,400 --> 00:57:42,400
Never.
